                    <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Shopping &mdash;</h3>
                    <p>Having easy access to shopping complexes, malls, and stores can save you a lot of trouble and time on regular occasions.</p>
                    <p>When it comes to shopping, the Tuscany Market is a great shopping complex that is near the centre of the Tuscany community. This complex is full of various stores and will help you find whatever you are looking for within the neighbourhood itself.</p>
                    <p>When it comes to regular groceries and supplies for your home, this complex has a large Sobeys store which is the perfect place to find food and other things you may need to keep your home stocked. This Sobeys store also has a connected Liquor store which has a wide range of alcoholic beverages on offer.</p>
                    <p>It also has a Starbucks and Domino's Pizza, which are both great places for quick and delicious food. So, you won't have to go too far for a meal.</p>
                    <p>Apart from this, the area also has many standalone stores such as "The Shopping Bag Finds" and "Bumbleberry Toys" where you can find items such as clothing, toys, and much much more.</p>
                    <p>If you would prefer to spend the day at the mall, you can visit the nearby Market Mall where you will find a wide range of big box stores selling, makeup, food, clothing and more!</p>
                </div>
                <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
                    <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Parks &mdash;</h3>
                    <p>A great way to maintain positivity and peace in a community is with the incorporation of greenery and plant life. While this can be done throughout a neighbourhood, one of the most relaxing additions in this aspect is local parks.</p>
                    <p>Out of the smaller parks in the area, the Tuscany Ridge Green Playground and Tuscany Drive Playground are great for people of all ages. With an assortment of activities such as slides, swings, and much more, they are fun for both kids and adults to have a relaxing day out in the sun.</p>
                    <p>Tuscany is also home to Twelve Mile Coulee Park. This nature preserve includes two off-leash areas to exercise your pets, 190 hectares of prairie grasslands, numerous trails and walking paths, as well as benches sprinkled throughout the park to provide a resting point to enjoy the views. This natural grassland is home to countless varieties of birds and other wildlife and is a popular destination for photographers and outdoor enthusiasts throughout the city.</p>
                </div>
